Class ParserDomainTheory

  • java.lang.Object
    • ParserDomainTheory
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ParserSILKFile, ParserSILKFilePreXML

    public class ParserDomainTheory
extends java.lang.Object
    This Parser is an adaptation of the Mock-a-Java parser built for Nobo Komogata's Compiler class (CIS 341) in Spring 2000 at Penn. It is NOT an elegant or professional-quality parser -- just a utility to allow Domain Theories written in Horn Clauses to be read into Kinship programs and converted to the proper Java objects for reasoning there. The Context-Free Grammar defining a Domain Theory is documented in DomainTheoryGrammar.

    NOTE: All exception text in this class is intended for the developer in debugging,so it is not translated.

    When constructed with a Tokenizer, a Parser will construct a Kinship domain theory from the tokens found in the Tokenizer's input file.
